Third-party code
----------------

This project ports embroidery format logic from the following
open-source projects:

- pyembroidery (https://github.com/inkstitch/pyembroidery) — MIT License.
  The EmbCompress (Greg-Hus) decompressor, the ZHS reader logic, and the
  HUS/VIP command conventions in packages/core are TypeScript ports of
  pyembroidery source code.

- libembroidery (https://github.com/Embroidermodder/libembroidery) —
  zlib license. Used as format documentation reference; the files under
  reference/vendor/ are unmodified excerpts kept for reverse-engineering
  reference only and are not part of the shipped product.

The ZHS writer is original work, reverse-engineered from Artist Toolkit
output for interoperability purposes (see docs/ZHS_FORMAT.md).

Bundled assets
--------------

- Fonts: "Bricolage Grotesque", "Instrument Sans" and "JetBrains Mono",
  all licensed under the SIL Open Font License 1.1 and self-hosted (no
  third-party font requests at runtime, no CDN). The woff2 files live in
  apps/web/src/assets/fonts with their OFL.txt license texts alongside;
  the OFL permits bundling them in the site build and in the desktop
  and CLI executables.
- The three stage designs in apps/web/src/assets/designs
  (unicorn-6x10.jef, lobster.pes, octopus.dst) are designs the owner is
  entitled to publish; they ship with the site and desktop builds by the
  owner's decision. They are the ONLY embroidery designs in the repo.
- fixtures/ and the design-derived golden files under
  packages/core/test/golden are NOT in the repository: real embroidery
  designs (personal designs, community designs shared within the owner's
  group, and a factory sample shipped with a Zeng Hsing machine) used as
  private test data for interoperability work — not redistributable
  content. The test suite self-skips when they are absent; the full
  suite runs on the owner's machine.

